## I. Design Philosophy

### Core Principle: Visual Clarity Over Decoration

Every element must serve communication. No decorative flourishes. Clean beats cluttered. If it doesn't aid understanding, remove it.

### The Nested Hierarchy

Map content to slides using this structure:

| Level | Element | Guideline |
|-------|---------|-----------|
| 1 | Presentation | 3-7 slides, complete narrative arc |
| 2 | Section | 1 title + 2-4 content slides per topic |
| 3 | Slide | 1 concept, 1 heading, 3-5 bullets max |
| 4 | Element | 5-12 words per bullet, fragments not sentences |

### Content Density Rules

**Hard Limits (Never Exceed):**
- Slides per presentation: 7
- Bullets per slide: 5
- Words per bullet: 12
- Characters in heading: 50
- Characters in bullet: 80

**Optimal Targets:**
- Slides: 5
- Bullets: 4
- Words per bullet: 7-8

